Oleksandr Shelipov was killed outside his home by 21-year-old Vadim Shishimarin who pleaded guilty in the first trial for war crimes since Russia's invasion began. Mr Shelipov's wife, Kateryna faced the defendant asking: "Tell me please, why did you come here? To Protect us? "Protect us from whom? Did you protect me from my husband, whom you killed?" The soldier didn't answer other than to ask for forgiveness, to which he added: "But I understand that you won't be able to forgive me." FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES... 